1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Season 6 trailer for Game of Thrones (2011) - Iron Fist (2017) finds its Danny Rand - Taboo (2017) mini-series with Tom Hardy, produced by Ridley Scott - Renewals for Gotham (2014), Better Call Saul (2015), The Flash (2014) and Arrow (2012) - Superhero Roundup - Streaming Spotlight - Power Rankings - Twitter Questions.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: The Walking Dead (2010)'s 90 minute finale speculation - New Game of Thrones (2011) images and teasers - Netflix's new series for Voltron (2016) - Renewals for Brooklyn Nine-Nine (2013) and The Last Man on Earth (2015) - Superhero Rundown - Streaming Spotlight - Power Rankings - Twitter Questions.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: Season 6 finale of The Walking Dead (2010) - Showtime and Starz to release every episode of Dice (2016) and The Girlfriend Experience (2016) - Renewals and Cancellations - It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia (2005) renewed for three more seasons - Superhero Rundown - Highlights and Lowlights - Pilot Review: The Path (2016) - Twitter Questions.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: American Crime Story (2016) finale; - Game of Thrones (2011) new trailer; - Seth Rogen and Evan Goldberg developing The Boys (2019) for Cinemax; - Benedict Cumberbatch signs up for another series of Sherlock (2010); - Superhero Rundown; - Highlights and Lowlights; - Pilot Review; - Twitter Questions.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: The Defenders (2017) to begin filming at the end of the year; - Star Trek: Discovery (2017), the CBS All Access series, timeline revealed; - Renewals and Cancellations; - Superhero Rundown; - Highlights and Lowlights; - Streaming Spotlight; - Twitter Questions.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: A discussion of the Season 6 premiere of Game of Thrones (2011); - Steven Yeun has been cast in Okja (2017); - Mel Gibson to direct series adaptation of The Barbary Coast; - Baz Luhrmann talks upcoming Netflix series The Get Down (2016); - Superhero Rundown; - Highlights and Lowlights; - Pilot Review: The Night Manager (2016); - Twitter Questions.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: Netflix announces Marvel's The Punisher (2017); - John Krasinski to play Jack Ryan in an Amazon series; - Sylvester Stallone joins Antoine Fuqua's "Omerta" (????) series; - New episodes ordered for Wet Hot American Summer: Ten Years Later (2017); - The Russo Brothers announce a new series The Mastermind; - Superhero Rundown; - Highlights and Lowlights; - Twitter Questions.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: Supergirl (2015) rumored to be moving from CBS to The CW; - New set pics revealed for Iron Fist (2017); - Seth McFarland's new live action science fiction television series; - New Ryan Murphy anthology series Feud (2017) announced; - The Path (2016) renewed by Hulu; - Superhero Rundown; - Highlights and Lowlights; - Streaming Spotlight Twitter Questions.

9.title: The Upfronts
9.plot: This week, the panel discusses the Upfronts from the broadcast networks. - ABC cancels Agent Carter (2015), Castle (2009), Nashville (2012) and The Muppets. (2015) - CBS greenlights MacGyver (2016) and Training Day (2017); - Joel Kinnaman to star in a Netflix series, Altered Carbon (2018); - Confirmed: Supergirl (2015) moves to The CW; - Superhero Rundown; - Highlights and Lowlights; - Streaming Spotlight: Narcos (2015); - Twitter Questions; - Pick of the Week: Josh picks The Wonder Years (1988).

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: Ewan McGregor joins Fargo (2014) for season 3; - Michael Lombardo, HBO's president of programming, steps down; - Cary Joji Fukunaga to direct Stanley Kubrick's Napoleon miniseries for HBO; - CBS reveals logo for Star Trek: Discovery (2017); - Superhero Rundown; - Highlights and Lowlights; - Pilot Review; - Twitter Questions; - Pick of the Week.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: Netflix to stream all Disney properties in the initial pay TV time period; - HBO's Westworld (2016) series to be released in the fall of 2016; - Renewals and Cancellations; - Interview with Game of Thrones (2011)' Ania Bukstein; - Highs and Lows; - Streaming Spotlight; - Twitter Questions.

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: Showtime orders 20 episodes of Purity (2020) starring Daniel Craig; - HBO orders Bill Hader vehicle Barry (2018) to series; - Julie Andrews and Netflix team up with Jim Henson Company for Julie's Greenroom (2017); - Starz has ordered two more seasons of Outlander (2014); an interview with the showrunners of_"Voltron: Legendary Defender" (2016)_; - Superhero Rundown; - Highlights and Lowlights; -Pilot Review: Feed the Beast (2016); - Twitter Questions.

13.title: Episode #1.13
13.plot: The crew talks about the extended Game of Thrones (2011); - Kevin Smith to make a TV series adaptation of Mallrats (1995); - Amazon announces new pilots; - Superhero Rundown; - Highlights and Lowlights; - Streaming Spotlight; - Twitter Questions; - Pick of the Week.

14.title: Episode #1.14
14.plot: The CW finds its Superman for Supergirl (2015); - New season announced for HBO's Curb Your Enthusiasm (2000); - Making a Murderer (2015) directors to do scripted series, America's Most Admired Lawbreaker; - Game of Thrones (2011) discussion; - Superhero Rundown; - Preacher (2016) review; - Highs and Lows; - Pilot Review: Animal Kingdom (2016); - Twitter Questions.

15.title: Episode #1.15
15.plot: Game of Thrones (2011) season 6 finale; - Bryan Fuller talks Star Trek: Discovery (2017) series; - Mr. Robot (2015) season 2; - Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (2013) to introduce Ghost Rider? - Stephen Arnell talks violent Arrow (2012) episode; - Preacher (2016) discussion; - Highs and Lows; - Pilot Review: Roadies (2016); - Twitter Questions.

16.title: Episode #1.16
16.plot: The Russo Brothers will adapt The Warriors (1979) for television; - Lionsgate acquired the Starz family of networks for $4.4 billion; - Netflix orders 10 episodes of an adaptation of Lost in Space (1965); - Harry Potter's Tom Felton joins The Flash (2014) as series regular; - WWE star Cody Runnels joins Arrow (2012); - Preacher (2016) review; - Pilot Review: The Night Of (2016); - Highs and Lows; - Twitter Questions.

17.title: Episode #1.17
17.plot: Game of Thrones (2011) season 7 delayed; - The Walking Dead (2010) adds four actors as regulars; - Comic-Con TV schedule revealed; - Superhero Rundown; - Preacher (2016) episode review - Spoiler Alert: Josh and Perri discuss season 4 of Orphan Black (2013) ; - Highs and Lows; - Twitter Questions; - Pick of the Week: Sasha picks FXX's You're the Worst (2014).

18.title: Episode #1.18
18.plot: X-Men series in the works; - Steven Soderbergh on season 3 of The Knick (2014); - Kathy Bates joins new series Disjointed (2017); - Superhero Rundown; - Spoiler Review: Stranger Things (2016); - Highs and Lows; - Twitter Questions; - Pick of the Week: David recommends BBC America's The Last Kingdom (2015).

19.title: 2016 San Diego Comic-Con
19.plot: Comic Con trailers for Luke Cage (2016), Iron Fist (2017); - Comic-Con trailer for American Gods (2017); - Daredevil (2015) renewed for season 3; - Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (2013) announces Ghost Rider; - Star Trek: Discovery (2017) tease; - Sherlock (2010) season 4 trailer; - Recap: Preacher: Finish the Song (2016); - Recap: Mr. Robot: eps2.1_k3rnel-pan1c.ksd (2016); - Twitter Questions; Pick of the Week: Josh recommends The Goldbergs (2013).

20.title: Episode #1.20
20.plot: Game of Thrones (2011) to officially end after season 8; - The Duffer Brothers talk Stranger Things (2016), season 2; - Possibility of Arrested Development (2003), season 5; - First image of Superman revealed for Supergirl (2015); - Grant Gustin talks Flashpoint storyline in The Flash (2014); - Review: Preacher: Call and Response (2016); - Review: Mr. Robot: eps2.2_init_1.asec (2016); - Review: The Night Of: The Art of War (2016); - Josh and Perri quiz Scott Wolf of NBC's The Night Shift (2014); - Highs and Lows; - Twitter Questions; Pick of the Week: David recommends The A Word (2016).
